{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778991583048,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe4178cffellUqft2iQfYqxk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_5h75DG6CXIVkNP4BqS9FLpwW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated `GO:0045022` to remove the microtubule-specific wording from the textual definition, since that gloss is not generally applicable.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR `<NN>`.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated the textual definition of `GO:0045022` `early endosome to late endosome transport`.\n+\n+Summary of change:\n+- Removed the clause `transport occurs along microtubules and can be experimentally blocked with microtubule-depolymerizing drugs` from the definition.\n+- Kept the existing term label, synonym, logical axioms, and definition xrefs unchanged.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue requested removal of an over-specific mechanistic gloss from the text definition.\n+- The microtubule-dependent wording is not universally true across taxa and experimental systems, so the broader transport definition is a better ontology-level description.\n+- No logical re-axiomatization was needed; the existing vesicle transport pattern still fits the term.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- Pre-validation: `make travis_build` passed before edits.\n+- Post-edit validation: `make travis_build` passed after check-in.\n+\n+Workflow followed:\n+- Inspected the issue context and current term stanza.\n+- Checked out `GO:0045022` with `obo-checkout.pl`.\n+- Edited the local term file in `terms/`.\n+- Checked the term back into `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n+- Committed only the edited ontology source file.\n+\n+Checklist:\n+- [x] PLAN: issue reviewed and requested change understood\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: target term inspected in `go-edit.obo`